WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:08.008
[country music playing]

00:11.094 --> 00:13.013
Aw. There's an alligator
just walking around.

00:13.096 --> 00:14.723
This does not look like America.

00:14.806 --> 00:17.559
Girl, this feels like America
absolutely to me.

00:22.313 --> 00:24.774
♪ Hey, yeah ♪

00:25.859 --> 00:27.110
♪ All right ♪

00:28.445 --> 00:30.613
♪ Mmm, mmm, ah ♪

00:30.697 --> 00:33.074
♪ Yeah ♪

00:33.158 --> 00:35.076
♪ All right, whoo! ♪

00:35.160 --> 00:39.205
♪ Oh, things just keep getting better ♪

00:40.081 --> 00:40.999
♪ Come on ♪

00:45.003 --> 00:47.839
♪ Ooh, yeah ♪

00:50.133 --> 00:51.009
♪ Yeah ♪

00:52.093 --> 00:54.596
♪ Things just keep getting better ♪

00:54.679 --> 00:57.932
♪ Down in New Orleans ♪

01:00.101 --> 01:02.520
[accordion music
in Louisiana Creole playing]

01:03.938 --> 01:06.232
-[Karamo] Wanna know who we're helping?
-[guys] Yeah!

01:06.316 --> 01:09.319
Okay. His name is Ernest Bartholomew.

01:09.402 --> 01:11.321
Welcome to New Orleans. Enjoy yourself.

01:12.280 --> 01:16.868
[Karamo] "He is a proud Creole
who grew up deep in the Louisiana bayou."

01:16.951 --> 01:18.536
-The intonation, Karamo.
-The bayou.

01:18.620 --> 01:21.498
-Shiver me timbers on that "deep."
-[laughs]

01:21.581 --> 01:24.375
Growing up in the country, man,
I think that's the place to grow up.

01:27.003 --> 01:29.881
You know, my dad,
such a special person, such a character,

01:29.964 --> 01:31.257
and my mom puts up with him.

01:31.341 --> 01:32.717
Yeah, fantastic.

01:32.801 --> 01:37.847
"He's 68 years old and is about
to celebrate his 39th wedding anniversary

01:37.931 --> 01:39.140
with his wife, Miranda!"

01:39.224 --> 01:40.225
How sweet!

01:40.308 --> 01:43.144
Miranda, look,
she's a wonderful woman, you know?

01:43.228 --> 01:45.146
Real good. Beautiful.

01:45.230 --> 01:50.985
Ernest has the biggest heart
you will ever, ever encounter.

01:51.069 --> 01:52.821
[Ernest] Miranda grew up in the city.

01:52.904 --> 01:55.698
You know, I didn't want to marry
anybody down there from the country

01:55.782 --> 01:58.451
because it's a close relationship,
might be my cousin.

01:58.535 --> 02:01.538
-That is Ernest.
-[chuckles]

02:01.621 --> 02:04.040
"Ernest and Miranda's two daughters
have left the nest,

02:04.124 --> 02:06.376
and the distance
in their marriage has grown."

02:06.459 --> 02:08.920
-No!
-That's common, though.

02:09.003 --> 02:11.840
[Miranda] The girls moved out of state,

02:11.923 --> 02:15.677
and that's when
we started having separate lives.

02:15.760 --> 02:18.763
Cooking, you know,
doing my butterfly garden.

02:18.847 --> 02:20.056
He has his garage.

02:21.057 --> 02:25.019
If you want to spend time with me,
I'm outside messing around in my man cave.

02:25.103 --> 02:28.982
Ernest is tinkering on his car
all the time.

02:29.065 --> 02:31.401
My dad's always in his man cave
watching the game,

02:31.484 --> 02:35.446
and my mom is always in the kitchen
watching cooking shows.

02:35.530 --> 02:38.908
It's easy to burn rubber.
You just give it gas and pop the clutch.

02:38.992 --> 02:41.035
I'm very convinced
he could live out there

02:41.119 --> 02:42.495
if… if we would let him.

02:42.579 --> 02:46.499
A lot of times, couples with kids,
the kids become their everything,

02:46.583 --> 02:48.626
and when the kids leave,
they're like, "Oh, wait."

02:48.710 --> 02:50.795
"We forgot we have
nothing in common anymore."

02:50.879 --> 02:53.089
[Ernest] Miranda don't like
to do the things I like to do,

02:53.173 --> 02:55.258
go in the boat and fishin', you know.

02:55.758 --> 02:59.220
She said, "They don't have no bathroom."
I say, "Well, we got a bucket." [laughs]

02:59.304 --> 03:02.599
Riding the bicycle, enjoying the music.

03:02.682 --> 03:06.227
Yes. Country mouse
and the city girl, you know?

03:06.311 --> 03:08.605
We are very, very different.

03:08.688 --> 03:13.026
"Miranda loves trying new cuisines,
but Ernest is not interested."

03:13.109 --> 03:15.111
[country music playing]

03:17.572 --> 03:21.242
Before we got married,
we would go out to eat,

03:21.326 --> 03:25.205
but now Ernest would much prefer
to eat wild game.

03:25.288 --> 03:29.667
The stuff that I like to cook
is nutria, muskrat, raccoon.

03:30.460 --> 03:33.630
I won't clean it, nor will I eat it.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.466
It tastes delicious.

03:38.051 --> 03:41.346
"Their daughter Ariel is nominating
her dad before it's too late."

03:41.429 --> 03:43.598
Too late for what? That's ominous!

03:43.681 --> 03:45.016
♪ Bah, bah, bum! ♪

03:45.099 --> 03:47.602
[Ariel] My dad is very practical.

03:47.685 --> 03:50.271
You know, he's like, "I'll make sure
she has gas in her car."

03:50.355 --> 03:54.108
You know, "If she needs me
to pick up anything, I'll go and get it."

03:54.192 --> 03:55.401
We see the love.

03:55.485 --> 03:59.447
We just wanna see the love
how my mom wants to be loved.

03:59.530 --> 04:02.700
Miranda wants me to dress up,
look real nice and stuff.

04:02.784 --> 04:04.619
Yeah, I'm country, man.

04:04.702 --> 04:07.914
She married me, you know.
Like, it was good, so this is me.

04:07.997 --> 04:09.707
[Karamo] "As much as Miranda loves Ernest,

04:09.791 --> 04:13.253
she misses her cool man
who has now turned into a caveman."

04:13.336 --> 04:16.839
[Miranda] On a scale of one to 100,

04:16.923 --> 04:20.718
I love the rubber-banded beard

04:21.219 --> 04:22.303
zero.

04:23.930 --> 04:26.599
I think it's unique.
You know, like, I'm one of a kind.

04:27.100 --> 04:30.061
"With Ernest and Miranda's
39th anniversary at the end of the week,

04:30.144 --> 04:32.897
Ariel is determined
to help her dad get out of this rut

04:32.981 --> 04:34.732
and make this a special day for her mom."

04:34.816 --> 04:35.650
Cute.

04:36.859 --> 04:39.737
I would love to see them
meet somewhere in the middle.

04:39.821 --> 04:42.073
They love each other so much.
Like, he can do it, you know.

04:42.156 --> 04:44.075
I just don't think he knows how.

04:44.158 --> 04:45.159
"Our mission this week

04:45.243 --> 04:47.745
is to see if this country mouse
can charm his spouse."

04:47.829 --> 04:50.999
"Meeting halfway is more fun
than going the road alone."

04:51.082 --> 04:52.333
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

04:52.417 --> 04:54.585
-I'm glad we're together.
-Amen!

04:54.669 --> 04:56.671
[upbeat music playing]

05:03.052 --> 05:05.638
-[Tan] All right, let's do this!
-[Antoni] All right, let's go!

05:05.722 --> 05:07.640
Honey, we're home!

05:09.559 --> 05:11.102
[Bobby] Ooh, look at that car!

05:11.185 --> 05:13.146
-[Jonathan] Cute.
-[Tan] The house is really cute.

05:13.229 --> 05:14.272
[laughing]

05:17.608 --> 05:19.193
[Antoni] Where is he?

05:19.277 --> 05:20.903
-[Karamo] Ernest?
-[Antoni] Oh!

05:21.696 --> 05:23.990
Is it Doctor Ernest,
'cause I see you in scrubs?

05:24.073 --> 05:26.326
-Yeah, I'm… I'm a masseuse.
-[Karamo] Ah!

05:26.409 --> 05:28.953
How you doing? Karamo. Nice to meet you.

05:29.037 --> 05:30.538
-Nice to meet you.
-[Ernest] Yes, sir.

05:30.621 --> 05:32.540
Okay, Ernest is cute.

05:32.623 --> 05:35.585
A little scruffy, a little dirty,
but he's cute.

05:35.668 --> 05:36.878
Oh, fantastic.

05:36.961 --> 05:38.463
Is this car your actual car?

05:38.546 --> 05:42.133
I bought in 1986 for $1,500
from Voodoo Mike.

05:42.216 --> 05:44.093
-Oh.
-Come. Come see.

05:45.136 --> 05:46.637
[Tan] She's really pretty.

05:46.721 --> 05:48.306
Look at these interiors, honey.

05:48.389 --> 05:49.515
Wait, let me get this.

05:49.599 --> 05:50.683
Oh my God.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.977
Let's do a photo shoot!

05:53.061 --> 05:54.812
Check out that pistol grip shifter.

05:54.896 --> 05:56.022
What's that mean?

05:56.105 --> 05:57.148
Four speed. Yes!

05:57.231 --> 05:59.859
Oh, I'm out.
I don't know how to do stick shift.

05:59.942 --> 06:02.236
-This is gorgeous.
-Yeah, fantastic.

06:02.320 --> 06:06.491
I just clocked a massive TV,
so you don't just fix things in here.

06:06.574 --> 06:08.743
-Like, you fully hang out in here.
-Yeah.

06:08.826 --> 06:10.870
You and Miranda
should have drive-in movie date night.

06:10.953 --> 06:12.747
[Jonathan] Oh my God! That's cute!

06:12.830 --> 06:14.123
Man, fantastic.

06:14.207 --> 06:16.250
You have pictures
of your family everywhere.

06:16.334 --> 06:18.461
-[Ernest] Yes.
-[Jonathan] They're so cute.

06:18.544 --> 06:19.837
[Bobby] Beautiful.

06:19.921 --> 06:21.714
[Ernest] Dominique and Ariel, yeah.

06:21.798 --> 06:23.257
I got two girls, okay?

06:23.341 --> 06:25.218
Dominique was born, firstborn.

06:25.301 --> 06:27.053
Miranda showed her how to go shopping.

06:27.136 --> 06:28.471
Second born, Ariel?

06:28.554 --> 06:31.182
I go… I go fishing and hunting,
Ariel will come with me.

06:31.265 --> 06:33.476
[Karamo] I see you have
a lot of photos of your daughters.

06:33.559 --> 06:35.812
-Is there a photo Miranda up here?
-[Ernest] No.

06:35.895 --> 06:37.230
[Tan] Ooh.

06:37.313 --> 06:39.732
-[Karamo] Just was checkin'. Okay.
-[Antoni] Why?

06:39.816 --> 06:42.485
I go through
all the boxes of trash, you know, like--

06:42.568 --> 06:44.362
Don't keep digging this hole, Ernest.

06:44.445 --> 06:45.279
It's okay.

06:45.363 --> 06:48.449
Look, let me tell you… Let me tell you
about how I met Miranda.

06:48.533 --> 06:51.035
Now, you see, when I was
in high school in the late '60s,

06:51.119 --> 06:54.080
I was working part-time at Sears
in the back pricin' tools.

06:54.163 --> 06:56.707
-She workin' in the candy department.
-Aw.

06:56.791 --> 07:00.461
And she go in the refrigerator
to get the candy, close the door,

07:00.545 --> 07:01.796
hugging and kissing, you know?

07:01.879 --> 07:03.172
-She got…
-[laughs]

07:03.256 --> 07:04.090
Fantastic, man.

07:04.173 --> 07:06.134
Oh, we all know Ernest's favorite word.

07:06.217 --> 07:07.927
Fantastic.

07:08.511 --> 07:10.638
I notice that there's a lot
of food things here.

07:10.721 --> 07:13.307
I see a bit of organic honey,
some Louisiana hot sauce.

07:13.391 --> 07:14.809
I like to cook.

07:14.892 --> 07:18.604
-In… in fact, I just cooked some raccoon.
-Raccoon. Okay.

07:18.688 --> 07:19.772
Raccoon?

07:20.273 --> 07:21.190
Girl, please!

07:21.274 --> 07:25.069
I wanna see the grilled raccoon.
Let's see it. I want raccoon gloves.

07:25.653 --> 07:28.739
And it's smothered down
with wild onion, garlic, and hot pepper.

07:29.449 --> 07:31.534
Do you remember having raccoon growing up?

07:31.617 --> 07:33.035
-Oh yeah.
-Who made it for you?

07:33.119 --> 07:34.370
My mama. [speaks Creole]

07:34.454 --> 07:36.998
Why don't you give him some?
Let him try some.

07:37.081 --> 07:38.124
[Ernest] It's real tough.

07:38.207 --> 07:39.834
So it's kind of like a wet jerky.

07:39.917 --> 07:41.335
Antoni, don't do it.

07:41.419 --> 07:43.296
[Antoni] Can I have
some more peppers, please?

07:44.255 --> 07:45.590
There we go.

07:45.673 --> 07:49.427
Don't do it! Don't do it!
Don't do it! Don't do it!

07:50.386 --> 07:52.138
[Jonathan] Juicy, tender.

07:54.724 --> 07:55.600
Ah!

07:55.683 --> 07:57.727
Not only are raccoons absolutely adorable,

07:57.810 --> 08:01.731
they're the only animal other than humans
that can do this with their hands.

08:03.232 --> 08:04.400
And I just ate one.

08:05.318 --> 08:08.070
Oh, I'm so sorry. I've been so greedy.
Do you guys want a helping?

08:08.154 --> 08:10.114
-I just ate.
-Oh, I couldn't. I'm so full.

08:10.698 --> 08:13.743
Stop putting everything in your mouth!
[gags]

08:14.911 --> 08:16.037
This is my washroom, man.

08:16.120 --> 08:17.705
[Karamo] Where you wash the scrubs.

08:17.788 --> 08:20.374
[Antoni] This Nancy Meyers kitchen

08:20.458 --> 08:25.254
is stark contrast
to your living situation in the garage.

08:25.338 --> 08:27.840
-I really hope I get to meet Miranda.
-[Karamo] This Miranda?

08:27.924 --> 08:30.176
[Ernest] Yeah,
that's Miranda and Dominique.

08:30.259 --> 08:32.428
[Antoni] I love how you have
so many photos of everybody.

08:32.512 --> 08:34.055
[Ernest] Miranda put it all up there.

08:34.138 --> 08:37.058
Yes and yes and yes and yes.

08:37.642 --> 08:39.227
This is a bedroom or an office?

08:39.810 --> 08:41.604
-[Ernest] I use it to study.
-[Bobby] Okay.

08:41.687 --> 08:43.773
[Ernest] But that was
Dominique and Ariel's room.

08:44.273 --> 08:45.733
[Jonathan] Oh my God.

08:45.816 --> 08:47.485
[Bobby] Where is
your and Miranda's bedroom?

08:47.568 --> 08:49.904
-In the front.
-Okay. Let's check that out.

08:49.987 --> 08:51.072
Lead the way.

08:51.155 --> 08:53.449
Where does the magic happen?

08:53.533 --> 08:55.993
-[Antoni] Tanny, look.
-[Tan gasps] I love those.

08:56.077 --> 08:58.329
-[Bobby] Oh! She likes some shoes.
-Whoa.

08:59.914 --> 09:01.499
She loves a shoe.

09:04.460 --> 09:06.504
Okay, I'm not mad at a bomber jacket.

09:06.587 --> 09:08.047
That's not bad at all.

09:08.130 --> 09:09.382
These are in.

09:09.465 --> 09:10.967
[Karamo] Did you see the blue tape?

09:11.050 --> 09:12.426
-[Antoni] Oh.
-Oh, that's…

09:13.010 --> 09:14.428
Vintage.

09:14.929 --> 09:17.640
-[Bobby grunts]
-Did it work? Did you get it?

09:17.723 --> 09:19.850
-Be careful.
-He's pretty light.

09:19.934 --> 09:21.435
[Bobby] Wait! I'm gonna fall!

09:21.519 --> 09:23.688
-Oh God!
-[laughs]

09:24.689 --> 09:28.192
Are you a doctor, nurse,
or do you work in a hospital?

09:28.276 --> 09:29.402
No. It's comfortable.

09:29.485 --> 09:32.822
You can't find anything
that you like more that's comfortable?

09:32.905 --> 09:35.157
-Whatever.
-I wanna help.

09:35.241 --> 09:38.244
I'll help. Okay, tell me
what Miranda thinks of what you wear.

09:38.327 --> 09:40.162
She likes me to dress up, well-groomed.

09:40.246 --> 09:41.872
-Okay.
-[Ernest] I'm comfortable like this.

09:41.956 --> 09:43.791
-You know, it don't matter to me.
-[Tan] No.

09:43.874 --> 09:44.959
-[Ernest] Yeah.
-No.

09:45.042 --> 09:48.170
Sometimes you have to consider
the other person in a marriage.

09:48.254 --> 09:50.131
We'll figure out
the Miranda component later.

09:50.214 --> 09:53.676
So, first off,
how is this less comfortable than that?

09:53.759 --> 09:56.512
-That's very comfortable.
-Why are you in that and not this?

09:56.596 --> 09:59.432
I'm in the man cave,
"Oh, there it is." I put it on.

09:59.515 --> 10:02.435
Okay. When you're not in the man cave,
what are you wearing?

10:02.518 --> 10:05.146
-Probably jeans because I got--
-Show me.

10:05.646 --> 10:08.316
Nothing here.
Yeah, this is pretty much dress clothes.

10:08.399 --> 10:09.859
The rest of your clothes are?

10:10.943 --> 10:13.779
This closet is only for formal wear.

10:13.863 --> 10:15.823
The rest of the clothes are where?

10:17.074 --> 10:17.908
-So…
-[Ernest] Socks.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.118
-[Tan] Socks.
-As you can see.

10:19.201 --> 10:20.578
T-shirts.

10:20.661 --> 10:22.580
I've lived almost 40 years.

10:22.663 --> 10:28.085
I've never seen someone use
a filing cabinet as a set of drawers.

10:28.169 --> 10:31.589
This is mostly
your actual day-to-day wear in here.

10:31.672 --> 10:33.591
Right. Now, you see, the…

10:33.674 --> 10:37.428
The waist was too big,
so I put a cable tie on it, you know,

10:37.511 --> 10:38.638
instead of a belt.

10:38.721 --> 10:41.015
A cable tie works pretty good,
so I zip tie it.

10:41.098 --> 10:41.932
No.

10:44.018 --> 10:46.520
-No. No one's gonna take you seriously.
-[laughs]

10:46.604 --> 10:48.272
[Tan] This is all underwear?

10:48.356 --> 10:50.858
You keep your underwear clean?
No holes? That's not…

10:50.941 --> 10:52.485
It's practically a thong!

10:52.568 --> 10:54.195
That's a really loose thong.

10:54.278 --> 10:56.447
-This can never happen again.
-Right.

10:56.530 --> 10:58.074
Miranda's not interested in this.

10:59.075 --> 11:00.117
No, ma'am.

11:00.201 --> 11:01.661
And then talk to me about suspenders.

11:01.744 --> 11:04.080
You know,
I wear suspenders because it's functional

11:04.163 --> 11:05.873
and because I like to be unique.

11:05.956 --> 11:07.958
So you do care about what people think!

11:08.042 --> 11:10.461
-Pretty much, yeah.
-And yet you're still in scrubs.

11:10.544 --> 11:12.088
-[Ernest] Right.
-We'll figure it out.

11:12.171 --> 11:13.422
All right. Good deal.

11:13.506 --> 11:17.510
Ooh, someone's got expensive taste.

11:17.593 --> 11:18.719
[Bobby] Speaking of pictures…

11:18.803 --> 11:21.514
-[Jonathan] Ooh, Let me see.
-There's Miranda.

11:21.597 --> 11:23.683
[Jonathan] I love her Farrah Fawcett hair.

11:23.766 --> 11:26.644
Oh my God!
That's a picture of them on their wedding.

11:26.727 --> 11:29.730
-[Karamo] There we go.
-[Jonathan] Such young and crazy kids.

11:29.814 --> 11:30.856
[Karamo] They're beautiful.

11:30.940 --> 11:32.775
I'm gonna hold onto this photo.

11:33.359 --> 11:35.403
[Bobby] Some chipping paint
in the living room.

11:35.486 --> 11:36.821
[upbeat music playing]

11:36.904 --> 11:37.738
Huh.

11:37.822 --> 11:40.241
[Bobby] One of the things
that I noticed about the home

11:40.324 --> 11:44.036
is it feels
like they've kind of given up on it.

11:45.162 --> 11:48.374
Just like their relationship,
they've let the home grow stale.

11:48.457 --> 11:51.085
Oh. Okay. Okay.

11:51.168 --> 11:53.212
[Antoni] Oh, this is beautiful.

11:53.295 --> 11:56.465
-Is this your garden or Miranda's garden?
-[Ernest] It's our garden.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.384
-[Antoni] Both of you together.
-[Ernest] Yeah.

11:58.467 --> 11:59.969
My gosh, look at that monarch.

12:00.052 --> 12:03.139
[Ernest] Usually, they got about three
or five flying around all the time.

12:03.222 --> 12:04.432
[Antoni] Other than the garden,

12:04.515 --> 12:08.769
is there anything else you do together
that's special, just for the two of you?

12:08.853 --> 12:11.981
No. You know, like,
it needs to start to build back up.

12:12.064 --> 12:14.567
-Yeah.
-You know, build that relationship up.

12:14.650 --> 12:17.278
Add the proverbial and the literal spice,
if you will.

12:17.361 --> 12:18.571
Yeah, sounds good. [chuckles]

12:18.654 --> 12:20.197
This is called a hammer.

12:20.906 --> 12:22.324
This is called a screwdriver.

12:22.408 --> 12:25.453
When you need to level something,
you pull this out,

12:25.536 --> 12:27.329
and it tells you if it's level or not.

12:27.830 --> 12:29.039
You're welcome.

12:29.123 --> 12:31.417
-[Antoni] These are snap beans.
-[Ernest] Yes. They're good.

12:31.500 --> 12:33.294
Really good.
They have a nice sweetness.

12:33.377 --> 12:35.296
Ooh, those look like
hotter peppers, right?

12:35.379 --> 12:37.631
[Ernest] Yeah. Miranda likes spicy food.

12:37.715 --> 12:39.592
[Antoni] What's
her favorite type of protein?

12:39.675 --> 12:40.801
Fish.

12:40.885 --> 12:43.763
Wouldn't it be nice to make something
for her and blow her socks off?

12:43.846 --> 12:46.265
Yeah. Yeah. Fantastic.

12:46.348 --> 12:48.976
You failed the last time we did this.
Can you do it?

12:49.059 --> 12:51.145
-I can, but not with this pressure.
-Okay, go.

12:52.104 --> 12:53.105
No. No.

12:53.189 --> 12:55.357
-No!
-It's just falling down your body.

12:55.441 --> 12:56.317
[sobs]

12:56.400 --> 12:57.777
Don't fail again. Get it. No.

12:57.860 --> 12:58.694
Hold on. Hold on.

