No. I don't.

25:35.534 --> 25:37.911
Well, what's… what's… what's the key?

25:37.994 --> 25:39.412
What's the answer?

25:39.496 --> 25:41.248
You ever heard
of the five love languages?

25:41.331 --> 25:45.252
So the five ways that we need
to feel loved in our relationships.

25:45.335 --> 25:48.088
So, for instance,
there's words of affirmation.

25:48.171 --> 25:51.800
So some people like to wake up
and be like, "Girl, you fine."

25:51.883 --> 25:53.760
There's also quality time,

25:53.843 --> 25:55.262
receiving gifts,

25:55.345 --> 25:56.471
physical touch,

25:56.555 --> 26:00.684
and then there's acts of service.
"You need that done? I'll do it for you."

26:00.767 --> 26:03.019
Is acts of service
the way you need to be loved?

26:03.103 --> 26:04.396
That's not it.

26:04.980 --> 26:06.690
[Karamo] So this entire time,

26:07.274 --> 26:09.568
you think, by doing this chore,

26:09.651 --> 26:12.904
that you're showing her,
"Look, I'm still here, baby. I'm trying."

26:12.988 --> 26:15.365
-Acts of service are great, Ernest.
-Yes.

26:15.448 --> 26:17.993
[Karamo] But Miranda is saying
she needs something else.

26:18.076 --> 26:19.035
Right.

26:19.119 --> 26:20.579
And what do you need?

26:20.662 --> 26:22.706
Quality time and a lot of touch.

26:23.290 --> 26:25.792
Do you feel
like you get quality time and touch?

26:25.875 --> 26:29.004
Uh, you know, recently,
no, it wasn't like that.

26:31.298 --> 26:32.257
Used to be.

26:32.340 --> 26:33.466
What do you need?

26:33.550 --> 26:36.052
I need quality time.

26:36.636 --> 26:39.723
I do need touch and affirmation.

26:40.223 --> 26:41.474
-Words.
-Well--

26:41.558 --> 26:43.977
I know the communication is difficult.

26:44.811 --> 26:46.438
The words, I'm not good with words.

26:46.521 --> 26:50.817
I just need you
to let me know that you need me,

26:51.401 --> 26:54.779
because your independence
is sometimes very lonely.

26:56.698 --> 27:00.827
And I do feel alone in our marriage.

27:07.042 --> 27:07.959
[sighs]

27:12.005 --> 27:14.633
[crying] You know, she's special to me.

27:17.677 --> 27:20.639
And I know, for sure,
I could get it back together.

27:21.556 --> 27:23.600
I know, 'cause we special.

27:27.103 --> 27:28.855
Can you say to your wife, "I need you?"

27:30.231 --> 27:31.358
I need you.

27:36.071 --> 27:37.155
I need you too.

27:39.324 --> 27:41.534
Now, on the flip side,
because a relationship is two,

27:42.369 --> 27:46.665
he said he needs
more quality time and touch.

27:46.748 --> 27:47.749
And you both said that.

27:48.750 --> 27:51.336
When was the last time you all held hands?

27:51.920 --> 27:55.382
-When I was in the hospital?
-I didn't even know you remembered that.

27:55.465 --> 27:57.926
-So this is where the actions come in.
-Right.

27:58.009 --> 28:00.762
-So I think holding hands is a nice start.
-Yeah.

28:02.389 --> 28:03.765
[chuckles]

28:03.848 --> 28:05.600
-You did it on the sly.
-[Ernest chuckles]

28:05.684 --> 28:07.102
Let me see them holding hands.

28:07.185 --> 28:09.145
Oh! You sly with it!

28:09.229 --> 28:12.065
I see the player in you now
and why you got such a pretty lady.

28:12.148 --> 28:13.525
[Ernest] Oh man.

28:13.608 --> 28:14.484
-Yeah.
-I do see it.

28:15.485 --> 28:18.530
This is something that's simple,
that even in your busy schedule,

28:18.613 --> 28:20.990
if you can say, "I need you,"

28:21.074 --> 28:25.161
and if you can also stop
and just hold hands for two minutes,

28:25.245 --> 28:26.663
it's gonna be the first steps

28:26.746 --> 28:30.125
into you communicating the same way
in your love languages,

28:30.208 --> 28:31.710
because what's going on right now

28:31.793 --> 28:34.462
is not two people
who really don't wanna be in this.

28:34.546 --> 28:37.340
It's two people
who just forgot how to be in this.

28:37.424 --> 28:38.550
Yes.

28:38.633 --> 28:40.385
[Karamo] Ernest is so willing.

28:40.468 --> 28:43.263
You can see that he loves his wife
and he wants to change,

28:43.346 --> 28:46.933
and that's the first step
in reconnecting with someone you love,

28:47.016 --> 28:48.643
that desire to be better.

28:49.269 --> 28:51.229
We were going through a box in your house,

28:52.147 --> 28:53.481
and I saw this.

28:53.565 --> 28:55.650
[laughing]

28:55.734 --> 28:56.901
[Karamo] Do you remember that?

28:56.985 --> 28:58.653
[Miranda] I do remember it, yes.

28:58.737 --> 29:00.280
But I want you to look at that.

29:00.363 --> 29:01.698
[Miranda] Mm-hmm.

29:01.781 --> 29:03.533
[Karamo] Look how close those two were.

29:04.033 --> 29:06.161
Those two people
knew they needed each other.

29:06.244 --> 29:08.121
Yeah, man, that's fantastic.

29:09.205 --> 29:10.707
I remember these people.

29:11.916 --> 29:13.042
[Karamo] They're not gone.

29:14.252 --> 29:16.254
[upbeat music playing]

29:18.131 --> 29:20.133
[yodeling]

29:28.850 --> 29:30.727
[Tan] Have you been to Rubensteins before?

29:30.810 --> 29:33.271
Yeah. I think twice in my lifetime.

29:34.898 --> 29:36.483
-After you.
-Thank you, sir.

29:40.403 --> 29:43.406
-When was the last time you came shopping?
-I couldn't remember.

29:43.490 --> 29:45.074
I think about 30 years.

29:46.409 --> 29:48.703
Like, 30 years
since you went into a store?

29:48.787 --> 29:52.081
Yes, 'cause my wife,
she would get anything for me.

29:52.165 --> 29:54.375
The end of this week,
it's your anniversary.

29:54.459 --> 29:57.170
You're putting together
something beautiful, right, Ernest?

29:57.253 --> 29:58.880
What do you think she wants?

29:58.963 --> 30:01.800
What she would like
is nice clothes for me to wear

30:01.883 --> 30:03.384
and go out with her, hang out with her.

30:03.468 --> 30:05.386
Have you ever considered blowing her mind?

30:05.470 --> 30:06.971
Not really.

30:07.055 --> 30:10.600
-You've had 39 years to do that.
-[chuckles]

30:10.683 --> 30:12.143
-You see where I'm going?
-Yeah. Yeah.

30:12.227 --> 30:14.521
Why have you not?
Be honest. I just wanna know.

30:14.604 --> 30:18.066
Because it's not in me.
You know, like, I'm more of a casual guy.

30:18.149 --> 30:20.318
-You have a wonderful woman.
-[Ernest] Yeah, fantastic.

30:20.401 --> 30:23.905
Who has stuck with you for a long time,
because you're clearly a wonderful man.

30:23.988 --> 30:25.907
However, I think she's just thinking,

30:25.990 --> 30:28.576
"After all this time,
I want my husband to be my husband."

30:28.660 --> 30:30.662
-[Ernest] Right.
-"Not the garage's husband."

30:30.745 --> 30:33.581
-Right, truly.
-Truly, like, real talk.

30:33.665 --> 30:35.625
I've been letting her down.
Really, I have.

30:35.708 --> 30:37.669
[Tan] So I wanna do something for you

30:37.752 --> 30:40.880
where it makes it really clear
to your wife you care.

30:40.964 --> 30:43.299
I know you don't wear
a lot of formal clothes.

30:43.383 --> 30:45.343
-You don't need to in the garage.
-Right.

30:45.426 --> 30:48.221
But, like, for a formal situation,
like a wedding reception.

30:48.304 --> 30:49.681
-Or an anniversary?
-[Ernest] Yeah.

30:49.764 --> 30:51.808
-[Tan] Maybe you need something for that.
-Yeah.

30:51.891 --> 30:55.687
[Tan] So anytime you wanna go for a suit,
but you don't wanna feel super fancy,

30:55.770 --> 30:59.399
I would suggest something deconstructed.
That means it hasn't got a lining.

30:59.482 --> 31:02.944
It's a little looser,
and so you don't feel so restricted.

31:03.027 --> 31:06.322
If you've got, let's say, for example,
a T-shirt and a pair of jeans on,

31:06.406 --> 31:08.116
and she wants to go out for dinner,

31:08.199 --> 31:10.368
just throw on a jacket,
and you're good to go.

31:10.451 --> 31:13.329
-You don't have to make a major effort.
-That'd definitely work.

31:13.413 --> 31:16.040
-[Ernest] Can I see these ones on, please?
-[Ernest] Yes.

31:16.666 --> 31:19.210
Love those. Leave them just here.
We'll pick them up later.

31:19.294 --> 31:22.297
You did say that you like your suspenders
'cause it's your thing.

31:22.380 --> 31:24.841
[Ernest] Yeah. I don't see a lot of people
that wears them.

31:24.924 --> 31:27.635
I love these versions.
I love that you wanna be unique,

31:27.719 --> 31:29.929
that you're considering
how you present yourself.

31:30.013 --> 31:32.056
What I don't wanna see again is zip ties.

31:32.140 --> 31:34.017
Zip ties started
before the suspenders.

31:34.100 --> 31:37.520
I'm sure they did,
and they needed to die a long time ago.

31:37.604 --> 31:38.438
[laughs]

31:38.521 --> 31:41.399
Don't wanna see zip ties
on your pants ever again.

31:41.482 --> 31:43.192
-Are you ready to try on?
-[Ernest] Yes.

31:44.027 --> 31:45.904
Whoo-hoo! All right, come on out.

31:45.987 --> 31:48.781
If you can just park yourself
right here for me.

31:49.657 --> 31:50.783
Bam, bam, bam.

31:51.367 --> 31:53.036
Mmm, mmm, mmm. Now,

31:54.078 --> 31:56.831
does that feel
a little bit more Ernest for you?

31:56.915 --> 31:57.749
Yes.

31:58.416 --> 31:59.834
It's fantastic, man.

32:00.418 --> 32:02.170
[Tan laughs]

32:02.253 --> 32:03.129
I love it.

32:03.212 --> 32:05.715
[Tan] You're just gonna walk around town
snapping those, are you?

32:05.798 --> 32:07.008
I love that he loves it.

32:07.091 --> 32:10.011
He clearly is feeling himself.

32:10.094 --> 32:11.721
I wouldn't be mad at this at all

32:11.804 --> 32:14.223
if you ended up wearing this
on a date with the lovely Miranda.

32:14.307 --> 32:19.729
However, you could start the date
looking extra swaggy.

32:21.689 --> 32:22.523
Fantastic.

32:22.607 --> 32:24.859
Tell me what makes it work for you.

32:24.943 --> 32:28.154
Well, it fits good,
and the material feels well.

32:28.237 --> 32:29.155
Real comfortable.

32:30.031 --> 32:33.576
[Tan] When was the last time
you saw yourself looking wonderful?

32:33.660 --> 32:34.786
Very long time.

32:34.869 --> 32:36.829
Is it nice seeing yourself this way again?

32:36.913 --> 32:37.747
Yes.

32:37.830 --> 32:41.709
What's the point of wasting it on scrubs
when you can look as good as this?

32:41.793 --> 32:43.503
-Ready to try something else?
-[Ernest] Yes.

32:47.256 --> 32:49.050
Ooh, I already love.

32:49.133 --> 32:50.301
Fantastic.

32:50.385 --> 32:52.220
Are you just being nice to me?

32:52.303 --> 32:53.930
-No.
-Last one, you said fantastic too.

32:54.013 --> 32:58.017
[Ernest] Well, this is more fantastic
than the other one, I think.

32:58.101 --> 33:00.603
-Tell me what you like about it.
-Well, it's camouflage.

33:00.687 --> 33:02.063
-Like I'm a hunter.
-[Tan] I know.

33:02.146 --> 33:05.692
This is more comfortable
and looks like it's more simple.

33:05.775 --> 33:07.443
You know, like, 'cause I'm simple.

33:07.527 --> 33:10.613
Could you actually see yourself
wearing things like this

33:10.697 --> 33:11.948
for hangouts with Miranda?

33:12.031 --> 33:15.618
Yes, and, you know,
I just know I'll blow her mind,

33:15.702 --> 33:18.788
'cause, you know, like,
it's… it's… it's blowing my mind,

33:18.871 --> 33:21.499
you know, like… Man.

33:23.042 --> 33:24.127
I… Oh.

33:24.210 --> 33:28.339
Everybody that knows me
is going, "Ernest?"

33:28.423 --> 33:29.841
-Yes.
-[laughs]

33:29.924 --> 33:31.801
[Ernest] And I know it. Yeah, man!

33:31.884 --> 33:34.053
[Tan laughs]

33:34.137 --> 33:37.557
Well, wait. I want you to try on
the glasses that I pulled for you earlier.

33:38.307 --> 33:44.439
I mean, Ernest, you look so darn good.

33:44.522 --> 33:46.774
Hopefully, you'll look
at your closet and think,

33:46.858 --> 33:49.902
"I wanna get dressed up.
I wanna make an effort for my wife."

33:49.986 --> 33:51.529
For sure. She deserves it.

33:51.612 --> 33:53.281
-[Tan] She deserves it.
-She does.

33:53.364 --> 33:55.324
-Can I give you a hug, Ernest?
-Sure, you can, man.

33:55.408 --> 33:57.285
Because I'm really, really happy.

33:57.368 --> 33:59.996
-And you're made me really, really proud.
-[Ernest] Yeah.

34:00.079 --> 34:03.374
The way you keep raising your eyebrows
at yourself in the mirror is amazing.

34:03.458 --> 34:04.417
[laughs]

34:04.500 --> 34:06.753
Watch out. Watch out.

34:06.836 --> 34:09.213
[swanky music playing]

34:11.382 --> 34:13.134
[Jonathan] Okay, we're here.

34:13.217 --> 34:15.762
Gorgeous Bluenote Barbershop.

34:16.888 --> 34:18.181
Go ahead, gorgeous.

34:18.681 --> 34:20.016
This is Invee.

34:20.099 --> 34:22.185
-How you doing, sir?
-[Jonathan] We love Invee so much.

34:22.268 --> 34:23.102
He's the best.

34:23.770 --> 34:25.730
-Ernest, can I take your hat off?
-Sure.

34:25.813 --> 34:28.274
He actually has
what we lovingly call a skullet.

34:28.775 --> 34:31.778
I don't know if it's because
I was your mom in a past life,

34:31.861 --> 34:35.615
I just think it's, like, so adorable,
this little curly hair right here,

34:35.698 --> 34:37.450
but his wife doesn't like it!

34:37.533 --> 34:39.577
Today is a story of, like, compromise

34:39.660 --> 34:43.664
and making sure that Miranda, your wife,

34:43.748 --> 34:47.126
still wants to hold your hand.

34:47.210 --> 34:48.044
[Ernest] Oh yeah.

34:48.127 --> 34:51.130
With your shirts off,
in a very respectful way.

34:51.214 --> 34:53.341
I don't think that's gonna make a diff--

34:53.424 --> 34:54.884
-[Jonathan] It does!
-It does?

34:54.967 --> 34:57.386
[Jonathan] It absolutely does.

34:57.470 --> 34:58.429
[laughs]

34:58.513 --> 35:01.432
-She said that she misses you.
-[Ernest] Yeah.

35:01.516 --> 35:03.684
And you guys live together!

35:03.768 --> 35:07.980
Yeah, but, you know, she's a cook,
watching the Cooking Channel.

35:08.064 --> 35:10.858
I'm in my man cave, watching sports.

35:10.942 --> 35:13.194
But what if you guys
just sat next to each other

35:13.277 --> 35:15.029
for, like, one TV show a week?

35:15.113 --> 35:17.573
Just as long as they don't have
any good sporting events on.

35:17.657 --> 35:20.159
My husband watches
figure skating and gymnastics with me

35:20.243 --> 35:21.494
even though he hates it.

35:21.577 --> 35:24.956
He's obsessed with gardening,
and I was like, "Ugh, gardening."

35:25.039 --> 35:26.916
-Like, "Kick me in the face."
-[laughs]

35:26.999 --> 35:29.669
Turns out there's this TV show
called Gardeners' World

35:29.752 --> 35:32.255
that I thought I hated,
but it's actually really cute,

35:32.338 --> 35:34.549
so maybe there might be
a cooking personality you like.

35:34.632 --> 35:36.259
But you'll never know if you don't try it.

35:36.342 --> 35:38.427
-Right.
-Can I take your bubble pony out?

35:38.511 --> 35:39.428
[Ernest] Yeah.

35:39.512 --> 35:41.097
I love how you style your beard.

35:41.180 --> 35:42.473
[Ernest] I got style, man.

35:42.557 --> 35:44.642
[Jonathan] You got such good style.

35:44.725 --> 35:45.726
You really do.

35:45.810 --> 35:48.396
It might be unique,
but it's one of a kind.

35:48.479 --> 35:49.772
[Jonathan] Here's the thing.

35:49.856 --> 35:53.484
If Ernest had his skullet and his beard
because he loved them,

35:53.568 --> 35:55.778
and that was his personal style…

35:58.114 --> 35:59.407
I would clap it out.

35:59.490 --> 36:02.243
So I think, like,
a nice little square thing on him

36:02.326 --> 36:03.286
could be really nice.

36:03.369 --> 36:05.121
But that's not how we've arrived here.

36:05.204 --> 36:08.457
We've actually arrived at this style
due to neglect.

36:09.208 --> 36:12.086
I'm gonna start by cutting his mullet off,
then we'll shape it.

36:12.170 --> 36:13.588
It's coming off, Ernest.

36:15.131 --> 36:16.591
Oh Lord.

36:19.427 --> 36:22.638
♪ Don't it feel so good to be alive ♪

36:22.722 --> 36:23.890
[Jonathan] Ooh.

36:24.390 --> 36:25.933
Hello, jaw.

36:26.684 --> 36:29.604
I do love your big-ass mustache.

36:30.188 --> 36:33.149
Should we do
a little handlebar on him for fun?

36:33.232 --> 36:34.150
Yeah, for sure.

36:34.233 --> 36:37.361
[Jonathan] You are giving me
men's magazine,

36:37.445 --> 36:39.572
Men's Fitness, Men's Health.

36:39.655 --> 36:42.909
-What's your favorite thing about Miranda?
-[Ernest] She's just all around.

36:42.992 --> 36:46.078
You know, like, her mind,
you know, like, the way she thinks.

36:46.162 --> 36:46.996
Mm-hmm.

36:47.079 --> 36:49.790
-What's your favorite physical thing?
-[Ernest] Miranda?

36:49.874 --> 36:51.042
Her lips.

36:51.125 --> 36:52.668
-[Jonathan] Ooh!
-[laughs]

36:52.752 --> 36:54.045
Curveball!

36:54.128 --> 36:56.839
-She does have a pretty smile.
-Yeah.

36:56.923 --> 37:00.051
Because here's the thing.
Everyone wants to feel wanted and needed.

37:00.134 --> 37:01.469
-Right.
-By their partner.

37:01.552 --> 37:02.929
-[Ernest] Right.
-You included.

37:03.012 --> 37:06.265
So that means that you both
have to celebrate your partner more.

37:06.349 --> 37:07.558
-I will.
-[Jonathan] Yeah!

37:07.642 --> 37:10.186
You'll be able
to show up for Miranda better.

37:10.269 --> 37:11.604
-That makes sense, right?
-Yes.

37:11.687 --> 37:13.397
Yes. Yes. Yes.

37:13.481 --> 37:17.109
-This is a mustache wax that I like.
-[Ernest] Okay.

37:17.193 --> 37:19.070
I just took a little teeny tiny bit.

37:19.153 --> 37:21.822
Then you take your index finger,
set the hair on there,

37:21.906 --> 37:25.576
and I just like, push the wax on my finger
to, like, bend it upwards.

37:26.702 --> 37:28.496
And, my God, does he look gorgeous?

37:28.579 --> 37:31.374
Have we done such a good job,
or have we done such a good job?

37:31.457 --> 37:32.583
-Look at him!
-[Invee] Right?

37:32.667 --> 37:34.085
You are so cute.

37:34.168 --> 37:35.127
Do you know?

37:36.254 --> 37:37.964
-[Ernest] Yeah.
-You do, right?

37:38.047 --> 37:40.174
-'Cause you are…
-[Ernest] Gorgeous?

37:40.258 --> 37:41.342
-You are…
-[Ernest] Gorgeous.

37:41.425 --> 37:42.510
-You are…
-[Ernest] Gorgeous.

37:42.593 --> 37:45.304
-Yes, you are! Ready to see your new look?
-[Ernest] Yes.

37:45.388 --> 37:47.056
Ready? Three, two, one.

37:49.016 --> 37:50.226
Oh! [chuckles]

37:50.309 --> 37:52.436
Lord! Watch out!

37:52.520 --> 37:53.646
[Jonathan] Right?

37:53.729 --> 37:54.855
When we take this off…

37:54.939 --> 37:58.109
-Yes, indeed.
-Oh my gosh!

37:58.192 --> 38:00.111
Oh yeah, Miranda, you gonna be surprised.

38:01.320 --> 38:03.447
Oh, I like this. Yes.

38:03.531 --> 38:05.908
-[Jonathan] That gave me chills.
-That's unique. I like that.

38:05.992 --> 38:08.619
♪ Oh, I got love running in my soul ♪

38:08.703 --> 38:11.831
♪ I got your love running in my soul ♪

38:11.914 --> 38:14.583
♪ I got love running in my soul ♪

38:14.667 --> 38:17.712
♪Gonna make me smile ♪

38:17.795 --> 38:20.631
♪ Oh, I got love running in my soul ♪

38:20.715 --> 38:23.592
♪ I got your love running in my soul ♪

38:23.676 --> 38:26.304
♪ I got love running in my soul ♪

38:26.387 --> 38:29.724
♪ Gonna make me smile ♪

38:30.391 --> 38:31.392
♪ Whoa, yeah ♪

38:33.269 --> 38:37.273
-I'm excited for you to see the house.
-I sure hope I don't pass out, man.

38:37.356 --> 38:38.232
[laughs]

38:38.316 --> 38:39.650
-[horn honks]
-[Ernest laughs]

38:39.734 --> 38:43.487
-[Bobby] Ooh! They're here!
-Let's go! Put the produce down.

38:43.571 --> 38:44.613
[Tan] Whoo-hoo!

38:44.697 --> 38:45.948
[Bobby] Hello!

38:46.032 --> 38:48.409
Come on, you handsome man.
Good to see you, sir.

38:48.492 --> 38:49.660
How are you?

38:49.744 --> 38:52.038
-[Ernest] Great.
-Your beard looks so good!

38:52.121 --> 38:54.290
-[Bobby] Ready to see your new place?
-Yes.

38:54.915 --> 38:56.792
Oh Lord!

38:56.876 --> 38:59.378
[laughing]

38:59.462 --> 39:00.671
[Ernest] Man, look at…

39:00.755 --> 39:02.173
[jazzy music playing]

39:03.966 --> 39:06.469
Hot dog! [laughs]

39:08.929 --> 39:11.682
[Bobby] So made this
much more comfortable.

39:11.766 --> 39:13.100
We painted.

39:13.184 --> 39:15.311
[Ernest] I told Miranda
I was gonna take care of it.

39:15.394 --> 39:16.312
I'm glad I didn't.

39:16.395 --> 39:18.105
[laughing]

39:19.148 --> 39:20.024
[Bobby] And then…

39:20.107 --> 39:21.567
[Ernest] Oh!

39:21.650 --> 39:25.488
-[Jonathan] No more cracking paint, honey.
-[Bobby] Miranda's gonna be very happy.

39:26.530 --> 39:28.407
Come and see your new bedroom.

39:28.491 --> 39:30.284
Oh! Whoa!

39:30.868 --> 39:31.702
Oh!

39:31.786 --> 39:33.329
[jubilant music playing]

39:35.081 --> 39:38.042
[Bobby] You might ask yourself,
"Wait, where's the bed?"

39:38.125 --> 39:39.668
-[Ernest] Yeah.
-I gave this to Miranda.

39:39.752 --> 39:42.171
-Yeah, she needs it. It's good.
-[Bobby laughs]

39:42.838 --> 39:45.841
-How do you think Miranda's gonna feel?
-[Ernest] I don't think she'll faint.

39:45.925 --> 39:47.385
But it'd come close to it.

39:47.885 --> 39:52.014
-[Antoni] Bobby, this room is beautiful.
-[Jonathan] I'm so obsessed with this.

39:52.098 --> 39:55.017
-[Bobby] All right, you ready to see more?
-Ooh! Wait.

39:55.101 --> 39:56.519
-[Tan laughs]
-All right.

39:56.602 --> 39:58.020
-[Karamo] He's ready.
-I'm ready now.

40:00.231 --> 40:01.857
Oh man!

40:07.738 --> 40:09.824
Oh man! [laughs]

40:11.492 --> 40:14.078
[Bobby] This was your desk.
You had a great desk already.

40:14.161 --> 40:15.663
I reused a lot of your furniture

40:15.746 --> 40:18.082
'cause you had
a lot of really beautiful pieces.

40:18.833 --> 40:20.251
Lord have mercy.

40:20.334 --> 40:22.211
-[Bobby] You remember these?
-[Ernest] Oh man.

40:22.294 --> 40:24.630
[mellow music playing]

40:28.926 --> 40:30.136
Oh!

40:30.219 --> 40:32.805
[Bobby] Every year, I want you
to take a selfie together

40:32.888 --> 40:35.057
to show the memories you're still making.

40:35.141 --> 40:36.475
Oh man! Y'all good.

40:36.559 --> 40:37.643
[Bobby laughs]

40:37.726 --> 40:40.146
-Thank you.
-Y'all outstanding, man.

40:40.229 --> 40:41.272
[laughs]

40:41.355 --> 40:43.649
-Oh man.
-[Karamo] Oh.

40:43.732 --> 40:44.984
[Bobby] You deserve this.

40:45.067 --> 40:46.819
You good? You're good.

40:46.902 --> 40:48.404
[Ernest] Man!

40:50.239 --> 40:52.283
Oh! Oh!

40:52.366 --> 40:53.659
Ooh!

40:53.742 --> 40:55.953
[upbeat music playing]

40:59.707 --> 41:01.083
Oh boy! [chuckles]

41:03.294 --> 41:05.337
-[Bobby] You're starting a new life.
-[Ernest] Right.

41:05.421 --> 41:09.300
But I didn't want to get rid
of a lot of the memories you made, so…

41:09.800 --> 41:11.844
-I kept this.
-[Ernest laughs]

41:12.845 --> 41:15.055
[Bobby]
Look, it's the girls' height measurements.

41:15.139 --> 41:20.060
I never told y'all to keep that, you know.
I'm so glad you did. [sighs]

41:20.144 --> 41:21.770
Lord! Lord! Lord!

41:21.854 --> 41:22.897
Man! [chuckles]

41:23.606 --> 41:24.482
Fantastic.

41:24.565 --> 41:26.692
Oh Lord! Lord! Lord!

41:27.735 --> 41:28.819
[Bobby] I put the door there

41:28.903 --> 41:31.614
so there is a connection
from your space together

41:31.697 --> 41:33.574
into your spaces outside.

41:33.657 --> 41:35.659
A door? [chuckles]

41:36.285 --> 41:38.662
[Bobby] This home
has had a lot of memories.

41:38.746 --> 41:39.997
And this room specifically.

41:40.080 --> 41:42.166
This is where
your amazing daughters grew up.

41:42.249 --> 41:44.585
But I wanted to put you guys back here

41:44.668 --> 41:46.462
because I want this to be closer

41:46.545 --> 41:48.339
to that place
you wanna hang out all the time.

41:48.422 --> 41:49.924
-[Ernest] Outstanding.
-[Antoni] Ernest?

41:50.007 --> 41:52.092
-[Ernest] Yeah?
-[Antoni] You can't handle what's next.

41:52.176 --> 41:53.177
I'm ready.

41:55.179 --> 41:56.430
Oh man!

41:56.514 --> 41:58.891
[upbeat music playing]

41:58.974 --> 42:00.976
Oh Lord! Lord!

42:01.060 --> 42:02.478
Oh man!

42:08.192 --> 42:09.818
-[Bobby] A whole new world.
-[Ernest] Yeah.

42:09.902 --> 42:15.449
So I wanted to bridge the gap
between man cave garage and house,

42:15.533 --> 42:18.202
so you guys have that space
where you can come in the middle.

42:18.285 --> 42:21.163
Now y'all can have either dinner
just the two of you,

42:21.247 --> 42:23.499
you can have the girls over,

42:23.582 --> 42:25.501
you can have friends over.

42:26.001 --> 42:28.879
-What do you think of it all?
-That's gonna blow Miranda's mind.

42:28.963 --> 42:30.714
This is outstanding.

42:31.340 --> 42:32.424
[Tan] What do you think?

42:32.508 --> 42:33.384
Fantastic.

42:33.467 --> 42:36.428
First off,
I actually really like your overalls.

42:36.512 --> 42:39.139
On a casual day
when you just wanna hang out, wear 'em.

42:39.223 --> 42:40.099
Oh yeah.

42:40.182 --> 42:42.977
But remember this is about Miranda,
not just you.

42:43.060 --> 42:43.894
Right.

42:43.978 --> 42:47.273
So one day a week,
you are going to dress nicely.

42:47.356 --> 42:48.232
[Ernest] For sure.

42:48.315 --> 42:50.568
That means something from this closet.

42:50.651 --> 42:52.152
-[Ernest] For sure.
-Not the garage.

42:52.236 --> 42:53.904
For sure. [chuckles]

42:53.988 --> 42:56.615
-All right, kids. Ready for this?
-[guys] Yeah!

42:56.699 --> 42:58.826
[Tan] Okay, Ernest, sir,
will you please join us?

42:58.909 --> 43:00.828
This is what he's gonna wear for his date.

43:00.911 --> 43:02.538
-Yay, date!
-For his anniversary.

43:02.621 --> 43:03.706
Yay, anniversary!

43:03.789 --> 43:06.041
-[Tan] Sir, would you join me, please?
-Ernest!

43:06.125 --> 43:07.376
[guys] Ah!

43:07.459 --> 43:08.836
[laughing]

43:08.919 --> 43:11.005
[Karamo] Wow.

43:11.088 --> 43:12.214
Fantastic, man.

43:12.298 --> 43:13.924
[Tan] He's 68!

43:14.008 --> 43:14.842
So cute.

43:14.925 --> 43:16.135
[Karamo] You look great!

43:16.218 --> 43:17.595
I know. I feel great too.

43:17.678 --> 43:19.430
You actually can make
a ton of money modeling.

43:19.513 --> 43:20.598
Fantastic.

43:20.681 --> 43:22.600
I didn't want just suspenders
that are functional.

43:22.683 --> 43:25.894
I wanted ones that look lovely,
which is why we got leather suspenders.

43:25.978 --> 43:27.229
-[Ernest] Yes.
-And the hat.

43:27.313 --> 43:29.982
I love a little pork-pie hat,
but a summer version?

43:30.065 --> 43:31.942
I can tell how much you love this outfit.

43:32.026 --> 43:35.195
Just the way that you were
carrying your hands in your pockets.

43:35.279 --> 43:36.989
It is so Ernest, and I love it.

43:37.072 --> 43:39.491
-Gee, it's outstanding.
-[Antoni] Good, right?

43:39.575 --> 43:42.328
-Outstanding. Yes.
-[Bobby] How do you think Miranda'll feel?

43:42.411 --> 43:45.205
-It will definitely turn her on.
-Whoo!

43:45.289 --> 43:46.665
-Okay.
-Yeah!

43:47.583 --> 43:49.084
-Come on, kids.
-Yeah.

43:49.168 --> 43:52.129
This is the time when we leave you
to enjoy your evening.

43:52.212 --> 43:53.881
This is your anniversary tonight.

43:53.964 --> 43:57.051
We need this to be your reset button,
and you've turned up for that.

43:57.134 --> 43:59.094
-For sure.
-At the beginning of this week,

43:59.178 --> 44:00.763
what were you hoping would happen?

44:00.846 --> 44:04.099
That Miranda and I would hook together.

44:04.183 --> 44:06.101
-Yeah.
-Contact, you know?

44:06.185 --> 44:07.853
I mean, what y'all did for me?

44:08.604 --> 44:09.938
Lord. Lord. Lord.

44:10.022 --> 44:11.940
I really appreciate.

44:12.024 --> 44:14.735
Appreciate it to the top, man. To the top.

44:14.818 --> 44:16.070
-Bring it in here.
-[Ernest] Yes.

44:16.153 --> 44:18.113
-[Jonathan] Tell the girls bye.
-[Ernest] I will.

44:18.197 --> 44:19.073
We're gonna miss you.

44:19.156 --> 44:21.700
Enjoy your anniversary.
I hope you have a wonderful time.

44:21.784 --> 44:23.202
-I sure will.
-Yeah.

44:23.285 --> 44:25.287
-Come on. Need a hand, Jackie?
-No, I got it.

44:25.371 --> 44:26.997
-You feeling good?
-[Jonathan] Yeah.

44:27.581 --> 44:28.874
[Tan] Have fun!

44:28.957 --> 44:30.042
I sure will.

44:30.626 --> 44:32.086
-Bye!
-Bye, Ernest!

44:32.169 --> 44:33.253
[Bobby] Bye, supermodel.

44:33.337 --> 44:34.338
[Jonathan] Have fun!

44:34.421 --> 44:35.839
[Karamo] He's so cute!

44:35.923 --> 44:37.925
[swanky music playing]

44:47.518 --> 44:49.520
[Bobby] ♪ What you doing? ♪

44:49.603 --> 44:51.689
Are you all hungry
for some raccoon skewers?

44:51.772 --> 44:54.733
-I'm done. You said raccoon skewers?
-[Bobby and Karamo] Bye!

44:54.817 --> 44:56.360
It's chicken, you Muppets.

44:56.443 --> 44:57.444
[Karamo] Okay.

44:57.528 --> 44:58.946
[Antoni] Hello.

44:59.029 --> 45:01.949
-[Antoni] Can I wear the raccoon hat?
-[Karamo] Won't you mess up your hair?

45:02.032 --> 45:04.702
-Are you gonna be Davy Crockett?
-So you know, this is vintage.

45:04.785 --> 45:06.412
It's not new.

45:06.495 --> 45:08.956
It's a little homage to Ernest.

45:09.039 --> 45:10.040
-Hi!
-Hi!

45:10.124 --> 45:13.043
-[Jonathan] Should we go watch Ernest?
-I already have beverages set up.

45:13.127 --> 45:14.253
Let's go. Come on, Neon.

45:14.336 --> 45:15.754
Aw.

45:15.838 --> 45:19.967
-Who's ready for Ernest and Miranda?
-[Antoni] Yay!

45:20.050 --> 45:22.845
-I am!
-[Jonathan] Their big anniversary!

45:24.596 --> 45:27.391
Look at how cute his little mustache is!

45:27.474 --> 45:30.602
-That man is good lookin'.
-[Jonathan] So cute.

45:31.395 --> 45:34.398
-[Karamo] She looks beautiful. Both do!
-Oh, I love that dress.

45:34.481 --> 45:35.357
Are you ready?

45:35.441 --> 45:36.483
[Miranda] Hey! Yeah!

45:36.567 --> 45:37.609
Are you sure?

45:37.693 --> 45:38.736
[Miranda] Yes!

45:38.819 --> 45:40.320
-Come on in.
-[Miranda] Hi.

45:41.780 --> 45:43.115
Look at you!

45:43.198 --> 45:44.783
Ah! Sookie-sookie now!

45:44.867 --> 45:47.411
-[Miranda] Hot model.
-[Ariel] Oh my God!

45:47.494 --> 45:49.288
[Ernest] They want me to model.

45:49.371 --> 45:52.082
They say, "Ern, you can make some money."
I say, "What?"

45:52.166 --> 45:53.751
You are a model, Ernest!

45:53.834 --> 45:55.711
-You better own it, Tyson Beckford!
-[Tan] Wow.

45:55.794 --> 45:57.880
Look at you!

45:57.963 --> 46:01.008
Aw, you look so good.

46:01.091 --> 46:02.426
Yes, affection!

46:03.385 --> 46:04.636
Look at you.

46:04.720 --> 46:09.141
The way she's looking at him,
I imagine that was her 40 years ago.

46:09.224 --> 46:11.935
-Show us around, guy.
-Come and see.

46:12.853 --> 46:14.104
What?!

46:14.188 --> 46:15.856
[guys] Ah!

46:15.939 --> 46:17.691
Yes, Miranda! Yes!

46:17.775 --> 46:19.651
-[Jonathan] So cute!
-No!

46:19.735 --> 46:22.154
Here comes a happy cry, I'm telling you.

46:22.237 --> 46:23.113
[Miranda] Oh!

46:23.197 --> 46:24.615
[Antoni] Bobby, this room is epic.

46:24.698 --> 46:27.826
-[Bobby] Aw, I'm so glad she likes it.
-Oh my God.

46:27.910 --> 46:30.996
You finally have room for your shoes, Mom.
Look, all these shoes.

46:31.079 --> 46:33.165
She wasn't expecting anything for her.

46:33.248 --> 46:34.541
Yeah.

46:35.834 --> 46:37.169
[laughs]

46:37.252 --> 46:40.088
[Miranda] Oh my, my, my.

46:44.134 --> 46:45.886
Holy smokes.

46:46.470 --> 46:48.347
I just don't have words.

46:49.056 --> 46:51.600
And I usually have lots of words!

46:52.392 --> 46:54.478
[upbeat music playing]

46:55.729 --> 46:56.605
Look.

46:56.688 --> 47:00.025
When we first started,
you know, as it goes on…

47:00.108 --> 47:02.736
-It just chronicles the years. Right?
-[Ernest] Yeah.

47:02.820 --> 47:06.281
Look. The empty spot, future.

47:06.365 --> 47:07.533
Yeah.

47:07.616 --> 47:10.369
[Antoni] I don't think I've ever wanted
to have a family more.

47:10.452 --> 47:12.996
I want that. I wanna look at a wall,
look at the photos,

47:13.080 --> 47:15.165
and see your entire life.

47:15.249 --> 47:17.292
[Ariel] We're ready. Open it!

47:19.461 --> 47:20.420
[Ernest chuckles]

47:21.171 --> 47:23.382
Oh wow!

47:30.097 --> 47:30.931
A door?

47:31.014 --> 47:32.558
[Ernest laughs]

47:32.641 --> 47:33.767
[laughs]

47:33.851 --> 47:35.602
You seen your closets.

47:35.686 --> 47:36.979
This is mine.

47:39.565 --> 47:41.942
Ernest, you have clothes!

47:42.818 --> 47:44.695
Are you gonna wear these?

47:44.778 --> 47:46.405
For sure! For sure!

47:46.488 --> 47:47.573
Oh.

47:49.324 --> 47:50.450
[Karamo] Yes!

47:50.534 --> 47:51.618
[Ernest] Ready?

47:51.702 --> 47:52.744
-[Miranda] Yes.
-Set…

47:54.997 --> 47:58.750
-[chuckles]
-Oh, guys!

47:58.834 --> 48:00.544
Look. [chuckles]

48:00.627 --> 48:03.130
Oh, guys!

48:03.213 --> 48:06.258
The week of growth was for him,
but this is all for her.

48:06.341 --> 48:08.719
Are you serious?

48:09.219 --> 48:11.889
-Oh my goodness!
-And look.

48:13.891 --> 48:15.893
[Antoni] The little butterflies!

48:15.976 --> 48:17.185
They have a home now.

48:21.940 --> 48:23.859
-Look at that one.
-[Ernest] Yeah, you love it.

48:23.942 --> 48:24.985
[Miranda chuckles]

48:27.112 --> 48:28.405
Aw.

48:28.488 --> 48:29.781
[Ariel] This is all for you.

48:29.865 --> 48:31.700
Oh, thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

48:31.783 --> 48:33.285
[Ernest] Thanks a whole bunch, girl.

48:33.368 --> 48:34.995
[Ariel] Yeah, no, enjoy it.

48:35.078 --> 48:37.205
-I love you.
-[Ernest] I love you too, girl.

48:37.956 --> 48:40.918
-Mmm.
-[Miranda] Absolutely beautiful.

48:41.001 --> 48:43.503
I think we could spend
a lot of time out here.

48:43.587 --> 48:44.922
Enjoy the rest of your night.

48:45.005 --> 48:46.214
-We sure will.
-Thank you.

48:46.298 --> 48:47.758
-[Ariel] I love you guys.
-Thank you.

48:47.841 --> 48:48.884
We sure will.

48:48.967 --> 48:51.303
[Tan] I hope my kids
are as sweet as Ariel one day.

48:51.386 --> 48:52.763
-[Jonathan] So sweet!
-Yeah.

48:52.846 --> 48:54.306
[Ernest] All right.

48:54.389 --> 48:56.600
-Look at this.
-What are you cooking?

48:56.683 --> 48:58.352
Okay, so this is a big moment

48:58.435 --> 49:01.313
because, as we all know,
the kitchen is Miranda's turf.

49:01.396 --> 49:02.230
[Ernest] For you?

49:03.649 --> 49:04.733
[Miranda] Salmon!

49:04.816 --> 49:05.859
-Yes!
-[Ernest] Fantastic.

49:05.943 --> 49:07.027
[Bobby] Oh!

49:07.110 --> 49:08.987
Hey, a departure in protein for him.

49:11.782 --> 49:12.616
[Ernest] Oh yeah.

49:12.699 --> 49:14.201
Shake and bake.

49:14.826 --> 49:15.744
Good job.

49:15.827 --> 49:19.414
-[Miranda] Oh, that's from the garden.
-[Ernest] Yes. Fantastic.

49:21.208 --> 49:24.002
[Karamo] It seemed like a salmon dish
is pretty easy to cook.

49:24.086 --> 49:26.797
It's a lot quicker than raccoon stew,
I'll tell you that.

49:26.880 --> 49:29.216
-[Tan] He plated that up really nicely.
-He did.

49:31.134 --> 49:32.719
[Miranda] Delicious. Thank you.

49:32.803 --> 49:35.013
-[Ernest] I amaze myself.
-[chuckles]

49:35.097 --> 49:38.392
He decided to compromise
and make something that Miranda likes.

49:38.475 --> 49:40.477
-To us.
-To us.

49:41.395 --> 49:42.938
You really look good.

49:43.021 --> 49:45.357
You look like your old self.

49:45.440 --> 49:47.359
-My old self?
-But new self.

49:47.442 --> 49:48.610
-I'm back.
-New self.

49:48.694 --> 49:51.446
-[Ernest] Yes.
-Glad to meet you, Mr. Bartholomew.

49:51.530 --> 49:52.656
[Ernest] Good.

49:52.739 --> 49:53.991
[Miranda chuckles]

49:54.074 --> 49:55.784
[Ernest] I love you, girl.

49:55.867 --> 49:57.911
It will change.

49:59.454 --> 50:01.039
You wanna marry me?

50:01.123 --> 50:02.416
-Marry you again?
-[Ernest] Yes.

50:02.499 --> 50:03.375
[Miranda] Yes.

50:04.001 --> 50:04.960
[Miranda chuckles]

50:05.794 --> 50:07.129
Aw!

50:07.963 --> 50:08.964
[Karamo] Look at that.

50:09.047 --> 50:10.716
That's so lovely.

50:10.799 --> 50:12.718
[romantic piano music playing]

50:12.801 --> 50:14.136
[chuckles]

50:14.720 --> 50:16.805
Ernest looks good, he feels good,

50:16.888 --> 50:21.643
but he also finally understands
how Miranda needs him to show up for her.

50:21.727 --> 50:24.521
You can find somebody
who lets you be who you are,

50:24.604 --> 50:27.399
but, on the flip side,
figure out what makes them spark,

50:27.482 --> 50:29.693
what they're passionate about,
what they love.

50:29.776 --> 50:32.904
♪ We got a love ♪

50:32.988 --> 50:35.157
♪ Can't be broken ever ♪

50:35.240 --> 50:37.284
♪ So throw it away ♪

50:37.367 --> 50:39.953
♪ We got a love… ♪

50:40.037 --> 50:42.831
It doesn't matter
how long you've been married,

50:42.914 --> 50:46.084
you still need to show up
for your partner.

50:46.168 --> 50:48.920
Remind them of why they married you.

50:49.421 --> 50:51.673
♪ So be a fool ♪

50:51.757 --> 50:53.759
♪ Oh, I don't wanna lose you ♪

50:53.842 --> 50:56.595
♪ I just want you every way ♪

50:56.678 --> 50:59.014
♪ I know it's true ♪

50:59.097 --> 51:01.516
-♪ You're so ♪
-♪ My arms are open ♪

51:01.600 --> 51:03.393
♪ I'm begging you ♪

51:04.811 --> 51:07.314
♪ Oh, I'm begging you ♪

51:07.898 --> 51:11.485
♪ To come back and stay ♪

51:13.445 --> 51:15.447
[quirky music playing]

51:18.658 --> 51:19.701
[Karamo] Voodoo.

51:19.785 --> 51:21.953
It's an often misunderstood practice.

51:22.037 --> 51:24.873
The religion was brought to Louisiana
by enslaved West Africans

51:24.956 --> 51:26.833
via the Caribbean Corridor.

51:26.917 --> 51:30.754
It's a religion connected
to nature, ancestors, and spirit.

51:30.837 --> 51:32.881
The core belief of New Orleans Voodoo

51:32.964 --> 51:37.094
is that one god doesn't interfere
in our daily lives, but the spirits do.

51:37.969 --> 51:39.513
Right, babies? [chuckles]

51:39.596 --> 51:41.181
Hi, Antoni.

51:41.264 --> 51:45.018
Antoni. Antoni. Antoni. Antoni.

51:45.102 --> 51:47.104
[laughs]

51:47.687 --> 51:49.856
["When the Saints Go Marching In" playing]

53:02.304 --> 53:03.597
[Ernest] Fantastic!
